      <h1 class="content-hero-title">MDMA: Effects, Risks &amp; Therapeutic Use</h1>
      <p class="content-hero-subtitle">MDMA (3,4-methylenedioxymethamphetamine) occupies a unique position in the psychedelic landscape &mdash; it is an empathogen-entactogen rather than a classical serotonergic psychedelic, producing states of emotional openness and empathic connection that have driven both its widespread recreational use and its emergence as a promising PTSD treatment. This guide covers effects, risks, neurotoxicity, the clinical evidence, and responsible harm reduction.</p>
